# TypeScript Conventions

## Types

- Define types as `interface` (not `type` alias) in `app/types/`
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- Use optional properties (`?`) for nullable fields

```typescript
import type { CV } from "~/types/cv";
```

## CV Data

- All CV content lives in `app/data/cv.ts` as a single typed object (`cv: CV`)
- When adding new CV sections, first add the interface to `app/types/cv.ts`, then update the `CV` interface, then add the data

## Utils

- Place utility functions in `app/utils/`
- They are auto-imported by Nuxt â€” no need for manual imports in components
- Export named functions (not default exports)

## Path Aliases

- Use `~/` to reference the app root (e.g., `~/types/cv`, `~/data/cv`)
- Never use relative paths like `../../types/cv`
